  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "nginx is a web and proxy server supporting HTTP and other protocols, with a focus on high concurrency, performance, and low memory usage. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* nginx: NGINX: Arbitrary code execution or Denial of Service via heap-based buffer overflow with crafted HTTP/2 headers (CVE-2026-42055)\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* nginx:1.24/nginx: \"HTTP/2 bomb\" nginx fix breaks module ABI causing crashes [rhel-9.8.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-191773)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
